            <def>The term usually refers to ordained monks and nuns, or can also include lay followers. In the later interpretation there is often mention of teh four assemblies (sìzhòng 四眾, skr. catuṣ-pariṣad), consisting of monks and nuns, laymen and laywomen
</def>
